---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About The Dispatch"
	description="What The Dispatch is and who it's for."
	pubDate={new Date('2025-01-01')}
	heroImage="/blog-placeholder-about.jpg"
>
	<p>
		<strong>The Dispatch</strong> is a no-nonsense tech blog covering software development, the
		modern web, and the tools and platforms shaping how we build things. Each post is written to be
		clear, direct, and worth your time.
	</p>

	<p>
		Topics covered include Cloudflare Workers, edge computing, Astro, modern JavaScript, developer
		tooling, and the broader landscape of the web platform. Whether you're a seasoned engineer or
		just getting started, the goal is to surface ideas that are useful and actionable.
	</p>

	<h2>Why "The Dispatch"?</h2>

	<p>
		A dispatch is a report sent quickly from the field — concise, timely, relevant. That's the
		spirit here. No fluff, no filler. Just clear writing about what matters in tech right now.
	</p>

	<h2>Built with</h2>

	<p>
		This site is built with <a href="https://astro.build/">Astro</a> and deployed on
		<a href="https://workers.cloudflare.com/">Cloudflare Workers</a> as a static site with edge
		delivery. It's fast, simple, and runs at the edge — close to wherever you are.
	</p>

	<h2>RSS</h2>

	<p>
		Subscribe via <a href="/rss.xml">RSS</a> to get new posts as they're published. No email
		required.
	</p>
</Layout>
